"title": "7735: leaders, political",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7735: leaders, political",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Since God is the ultimate ruler of all things, earthly authority derives from him. Although political leadership was exercised in various ways in Israel, there was always some overlap between political and spiritual leadership.</p>\n<h2>Israel had a variety of political leaders</h2>\n<h3>Judges</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg2:16\">JDG 2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg4:4\">JDG 4:4</a></p>\n<h3>Kings</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:1-1Sam8:21\">1SA 8:1–8:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:1\">1SA 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:1-1Sam16:13\">1SA 16:1–16:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam7:12\">2SA 7:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs1:28-1Kgs1:40\">1KI 1:28–1:40</a></p>\n<h3>Tribal elders and judges</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:7\">EXO 19:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut21:1-Deut21:2\">DEU 21:1–21:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth4:1-Ruth4:2\">RUT 4:1–4:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job29:7-Job29:12\">JOB 29:7–29:12</a></p>\n<h3>Foreign powers imposed rulers on Israel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke3:1\">LUK 3:1</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of those who were both political and spiritual leaders</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam7:15\">1SA 7:15</a></strong> <em>Samuel was both prophet and judge.</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:1\">EXO 34:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:27-Exod34:28\">EXO 34:27–34:28</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:25-Judg6:27\">JDG 6:25–6:27</a> <em>Gideon</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:4\">2KI 18:4</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr31:1\">2CH 31:1</a> <em>Hezekiah</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr6:31\">1CH 6:31</a> <em>David</em></p>\n<h2>Political leaders, like spiritual ones, were called by God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:31\">1KI 11:31</a></strong> <em>The prophet Ahijah confers authority on the leader of a revolt.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod3:10\">EXO 3:10</a> <em>Moses</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg6:14\">JDG 6:14</a> <em>Gideon</em><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:1\">1SA 16:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:6-1Sam16:12\">1SA 16:6–16:12</a>\n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa45:1-Isa45:2\">ISA 45:1–45:2</a> <em>Cyrus was a Persian king, yet he is described as God's “anointed”.</em></p>\n<h2>To reject God's leadership is to reject God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:6-1Sam8:8\">1SA 8:6–8:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:5\">1SA 8:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:19-1Sam8:20\">1SA 8:19–8:20</a> <em>Israel wanted a human ruler so that they might be like the surrounding nations.</em></p>\n<h2>Responsibilities of leaders</h2>\n<h3>To protect the weak</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:12-Ps72:14\">PSA 72:12–72:14</a></p>\n<h3>To administer justice</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps72:2\">PSA 72:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:8\">PRO 20:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:4\">PRO 29:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:14\">PRO 29:14</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa9:7\">ISA 9:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:3-Isa11:4\">ISA 11:3–11:4</a></p>\n<h3>To shepherd the people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:70-Ps78:72\">PSA 78:70–78:72</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek34:2-Ezek34:6\">EZK 34:2–34:6</a></p>\n<h2>Attributes required in leaders</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:1-Isa11:2\">ISA 11:1–11:2</a></strong> <em>Being anointed by the Spirit of God.</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:18-Deut17:20\">DEU 17:18–17:20</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:3\">ISA 11:3</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa11:5\">ISA 11:5</a> <em>trustworthiness</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov8:15-Prov8:16\">PRO 8:15–8:16</a> <em>wisdom</em></p>\n<h2>The failure of leaders</h2>\n<h3>Through exploiting their subjects</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:25\">MAT 20:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut17:16-Deut17:17\">DEU 17:16–17:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:11-1Sam8:17\">1SA 8:11–8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs12:4\">1KI 12:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer22:13\">JER 22:13</a></p>\n<h3>Through usurping religious authority</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam13:8-1Sam13:13\">1SA 13:8–13:13</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr26:16-2Chr26:18\">2CH 26:16–26:18</a></p>\n<h3>Through apostasy</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs11:7-1Kgs11:8\">1KI 11:7–11:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs21:1-2Kgs21:6\">2KI 21:1–21:6</a></p>\n<h3>Through trusting in alliances with heathen powers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa31:1\">ISA 31:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:12\">2KI 20:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs20:17-2Kgs20:18\">2KI 20:17–20:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:1-Isa30:2\">ISA 30:1–30:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:11\">HOS 7:11</a></p>\n<h2>Godless leadership is evil</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:32\">LUK 13:32</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:1-Dan7:7\">DAN 7:1–7:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev13:1-Rev13:3\">REV 13:1–13:3</a></p>\n<h2>People must have a right attitude to political leaders</h2>\n<h3>They are to be obeyed</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:1\">ROM 13:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom13:5\">ROM 13:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:13-1Pet2:17\">1PE 2:13–2:17</a></p>\n<h3>But obedience to God must come first</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:29\">ACT 5:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan3:18\">DAN 3:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan6:13\">DAN 6:13</a></p>\n<h3>Prayers are to be made for them</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim2:1-1Tim2:2\">1TI 2:1–2:2</a></p>",
